<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; SCHOLARSHIPS TO BE AWARDED AT DINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Flamenco dancers and a folklorico dance troupe are among the attractions at 
the Glendale Hispanic Business and Professional Assn.'s fourth annual Fiesta 
Scholarship Dinner to be held Wednesday evening. 
</P>
<P>
 Guests will be treated to dinner and Latin music during the event, set to 
start with a social half-hour at 5:30 p.m. at Casa Adobe de San Raphael, 1330 
Dorothy Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Association members will present scholarships to low-income students from 
Glendale who recently graduated from high school, association spokesman Jose 
Quintinar said. 
</P>
<P>
 Scholarship recipients include Glendale High School graduate Kathryn Ayala, 
who plans to attend UCLA, and Hoover graduates Susan Zelaya, who plans to study 
at Cal State Long Beach; Maria Garcia, who will be a freshman at Cal State Los 
Angeles in the fall, and Daphne Barragan, who will attend Glendale College. 
</P>
<P>
 Also receiving scholarships are Mike McCauley, a graduate of Crescenta Valley 
High who plans to attend Mission College; Barbara Rojas, a graduate of Daily 
High who will attend Glendale College, and Jose Omar Padilla, a Monroe High 
School graduate who also plans to attend Glendale College this fall. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the event are $25 for members and guests and $15 for students. For 
information or to make reservations, call (818) 382-4523. JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</TEXT>
