<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP SOCCER '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; SMOKE BUT NO FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gueorgui Alexandrov, a diehard Greek fan, was arrested in Chicago for throwing 
a smoke bomb on the field during Sunday's game between Greece and Bulgaria. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a Greek tradition to throw flares onto the field when the team scores," 
one officer told the Chicago Sun-Times. 
</P>
<P>
 One problem. 
</P>
<P>
 Greece has yet to score in the World Cup, having been outscored in two 
matches, 8-0. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
