<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP SOCCER '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; TOUGH FUTURE EITHER WAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The World Cup and the NBA Finals found a common bond -- somehow -- on the 
large message board in the display window of Adventures Unlimited, a travel and 
leisure bookstore and news stand in Long Beach's Belmont Shore. 
</P>
<P>
 It was scrawled in bright colors. 
</P>
<P>
 O.K., Gang, what's worse?  
</P>
<P>
 Being a Colombian soccer player and facing your coke and death-dealing 
sponsors when you get home.  
</P>
<P>
 Or.  
</P>
<P>
 Being John Starks and facing the NY press when you get home?  
</P>
<P>
 Well, Starks may have it tougher. Isn't the pen mightier than the sword? LISA 
DILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
