<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; PAUL WEST IS PROMOTED AT UNI DISTRIBUTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UNI Distribution Corp., the music distribution arm of MCA, promoted Paul West 
to vice president of studio operations, engineering and quality assurance. 
</P>
<P>
 West will expand the range of UNI's studio operations.He will also oversee 
quality assurance and engineering at UNI's new compact disc plant in 
Pickneyville, Ill., and its audiocassette plant in Gloversville, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
 West previously was director of studio operations, engineering and quality 
assurance. 
</P>
<P>
 * Castle Rock Entertainment has named Catherine Purves production supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
 * Turner Broadcasting System has named Libby Gill West Coast vice president of 
public relations for Turner Entertainment Group. She had been vice president of 
publicity and promotion for Sony Pictures Entertainment Television Group. 
</P>
<P>
 * Largo Entertainment has added three vice presidents. Mark Scoon was named 
vice president of production services, Heidi Lester was named vice president of 
acquisitions, and Robert Cotzo was named vice president of finance. 
</P>
<P>
 * Peter Schlessel has been promoted to senior vice president of business 
affairs and acquisitions for Columbia TriStar Home Video. He previously was 
vice president of business affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 * Hemdale Canada has named R. Bryan Tucker a vice president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
