<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SOUTH COUNTY; TUTORS NEEDED FOR ENGLISH PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tutors are needed to teach adults to speak, read and write English. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers will be trained by the South Coast Literacy Council. That group 
will hold an informational meeting from 7 to 10 p.m. Aug. 4 at the Irvine 
Auxiliary Educatio Center, 31 W. Yale Loop, Irvine.  
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers will teach illiterate English-speaking adults to read and write and 
teach English to others. 
</P>
<P>
 The South Coast Literacy Council has 350 volunteers and serves South County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
