<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; HEARING SET FOR DOGS' OWNERS IN MAULING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A pretrial hearing for a Burbank couple charged with various violations of the 
city animal code stemming from their dogs' attack on a woman as she was taking 
an afternoon stroll is set for July 21 in Burbank Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple, Edward Ecock and Andrea Valente, pleaded not guilty Thursday to 
misdemeanor charges of violating the city's leash law, harboring a dangerous 
animal and operating a kennel without a license. 
</P>
<P>
 Two mixed-breed pit bulls owned by the couple mauled Donna J. Smith, an 
employee of the Walt Disney Co., as she walked near the intersection of Parish 
Place and Chandler Boulevard on May 12. Smith required about 80 stitches on her 
face. At the time of the attack, the dogs were being watched by Valente's 
8-year-old son. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple's dogs, Cheyane and Dutch, are being held at the Burbank Animal 
Shelter until a judge rules on their fate. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
