<P>
WHERE ARE THEY NOW?; ROGER REPOZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times staff writer David W. Myers catches up with former Dodgers and Angels. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some Yankee scouts had tabbed Repoz, a left-handed outfielder, as the heir to 
Mickey Mantle.He made his debut with New York in 1964, but his hitting proved 
disappointing and he was traded to Kansas City before settling with the Angels 
in 1967. He hit 13 home runs in '68 and 18 in 1970. He left in '72 to start a 
five-year stint in Japan, where he became one of that country's most feared 
batters. Repoz, 53, is plant manager at Fabrica International, a carpet 
manufacturer in Santa Ana. 
