<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP SOCCER '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; U.S.-ROMANIA SOCCER DRAWS IMPRESSIVE 
RATINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The United States' World Cup game against Romania on Sunday at the Rose Bowl, 
televised by ABC, got an impressive 11.9 Nielsen rating in Los Angeles and a 
7.8 national overnight rating. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles had the highest rating in the country, followed by Seattle, 10.1, 
and Cincinnati, 10.0.New York drew a 7.1, Chicago a 7.0. 
</P>
<P>
 The 7.8 overnight rating is the average for the nation's 29 largest markets. 
The national rating for all markets will not be available until Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The highest national rating for a soccer game in the United States was 6.6 for 
the 1982 World Cup final between Italy and West Germany, also televised by ABC. 
</P>
<P>
 Other overnight sports ratings Sunday included 3.8 for the Greater Hartford 
Open on CBS and 3.4 for the Senior Players Championship on ABC. 
</P>
<P>
 In Los Angeles, the players championship, which led into the World Cup, got a 
4.0. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hartford golf tournament, which went head-to-head against the soccer, got 
only a 2.1. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
