<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP SOCCER '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; NO RESPECT FOR IRISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLIAM TUOHY, Times London Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One of the nastier press comments was reported in the Daily Telegraph, quoting 
the Jornal do Brasil of Rio de Janeiro. 
</P>
<P>
 "The anti-Irish columnist, writing under the pseudonym 'Verissimo,' says the 
Irish look like Norwegians pretending to be Englishmen and give the impression 
of having been selected by the 'HY' method." 
</P>
<P>
 This, he claims, consists of Jack Charlton entering an Irish pub at random, 
looking around at the customers and with the words "Hey, you," picking out 
those who have a "typical soccer player's face, or that of a criminal, or 
preferably a combination of both." 
</P>
<P>
 He then takes them to a nearby field where they start training -- "many with 
their pint of Guinness in their hands." 
</P>
