<P>
WORLD CUP SOCCER '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; MAYBE YOU SHOULD LET 
SLEEPING DOGS LIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFF HURST, The London Evening Standard 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The worst World Cup scenario, apart of course from the Republic of Ireland 
going out, would be if the United States failed to qualify for the next stage. 
</P>
<P>
 There were more than 90,000 people in the Rose Bowl to see their new heroes go 
down, 1-0, to Romania, and as my wife Judith pointed out as we watched the 
match: "What's it going to be like if the United States ever becomes interested 
in football?" . . . 
</P>
<P>
 If the Americans really are serious about making "soccer" a big sport over 
here, watch out. They will be turning out 6-foot 7-inch central defenders who 
can run 10 seconds for the 100 meters. 
