<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AST Research Inc.: Safi Qureshey, chief executive of the computer maker, said 
Monday he expects his company this year to take the No. 4 spot from NEC Corp. 
among the world's largest makers of personal computers. 
</P>
<P>
 Qureshey, speaking at the Bear Stearns technology conference in New York, said 
AST's annual revenue will hit $2.4 billion for its current fiscal year and that 
AST will have shipped more than 1 million PCs for the year ending June 30. He 
said the company will focus on its core market of selling to corporations. 
Consumer purchases should account for only 20% of sales, he said. 
</P>
