<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Met Life Agrees to Donate $2.5 Million: Metropolitan Life Insurance Co. said 
it will make the donations as part of an expanded settlement with Florida 
regulators over its marketing practices.Authorities found that the New 
York-based insurer deceptively marketed life insurance as a retirement or 
savings plan. The insurer has already paid Florida $4.3 million in fines and 
legal fees as part of a settlement reached in March with more than 40 states. 
Under the new agreement, Met Life also will pay $2.4 million in the next two 
years for programs aimed at combatting youth and family violence and preventing 
fraud against the elderly. 
</P>
