<P>
 Macy Narrows Its Loss: R.H. Macy & Co., operating under Chapter 11 bankruptcy 
since 1992, said its loss for May narrowed on fewer markdowns and better 
inventory control.Sales declined 4.4%, however, because of bad weather, the 
company said. The New York-based operator of 124 Macy, Bullock's and I. Magnin 
stores said it lost $15.9 million for the four weeks ended May 28, down from a 
year-earlier loss of $29.7 million. Before reorganization and interest expense, 
the company posted operating income of $6.4 million, compared to a year-ago 
operating loss of $7.4 million. 
