<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: IWERKS EXPECTS TO REPORT LOSS IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Iwerks Entertainment Inc., a Burbank supplier of special-format movie theaters 
and virtual-reality attractions, said it expects to report a loss for its 
fiscal fourth quarter ending Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The company previously said it anticipated breaking even or making a small 
profit for the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Iwerks attributed the expected loss to development of its Cinetropolis 
complexes, which will combine large-screen and motion-simulation theaters under 
one roof with virtual-reality rides, restaurants and shops. It also cited 
higher costs of installing a new giant-screen theater system and its 
virtual-reality product. 
</P>
<P>
 Separately, Iwerks said it sold three big-screen theaters worth a total of 
$2.7 million. The buyers are the Arizona Museum of Science & Technology in 
Phoenix, the Chicago Navy Pier and the Orlando Science Center. 
</P>
