<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: CALNETICS PAYS $4.4 MILLION FOR AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calnetics Corp., the Chatsworth manufacturer of molded plastic components for 
industrial uses, said last week that it had acquired all of the stock of 
Ontario-based Agricultural Products Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 Calnetics paid about $4.4 million in cash and notes for Agricultural Products, 
formerly a privately held company that manufactures plastic water-handling 
products, including tubing, filters and drip-system accessories. The company 
has plants in Ontario and Winter Haven, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 Lon Schultz, founder of Agricultural Products, has agreed to continue serving 
as president and director of the company, Calnetics said. Calnetics had total 
sales of $16.6 million for its latest fiscal year. Agricultural Products had 
sales of about $10 million in 1993. 
</P>
