<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: IMAGE ENTERTAINMENT REPORTS 4TH-QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Image Entertainment Inc., the Chatsworth distributor of movies on laser discs, 
reported net income of $648,000 for the fiscal fourth quarter that ended March 
31, compared with a loss of $13.8 million for the same period the previous 
year. Revenue for the fourth quarter was $12 million, down 30% from $17.1 
million in the same period the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the fiscal year, the company reported net income of $3.4 million compared 
with a net loss of $17 million in fiscal 1993. Revenues for the year were $66.2 
million, up 10% from $60.4 million the year before. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said fourth-quarter sales decreased because it was unable to 
remove inventory from its damaged warehouse following the Jan. 17 Northridge 
earthquake. It attributed the fourth-quarter profit to cost-cutting measures 
begun in March, 1993. Since last year, 17% of the company's work force, 
including three senior executives, have been laid off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
