<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PERFECTDATA REPORTS NET LOSS OF $402,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PerfectData Corp. of Simi Valley, which designs and markets cleaning ware for 
office equipment, reported a net loss of $402,000 for the year that ended March 
31, after posting net income of $514,000 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The downward turn was attributed to an $803,000 loss in discontinued product 
lines, including modems, cables and switch boxes for computers and printers. 
</P>
<P>
 The company has jettisoned such lines to focus on its core business of 
cleaning supplies and ergonomic office products such as footrests and 
copyholders, said Irene J. Marino, chief financial officer. 
</P>
<P>
 The company reported revenues of $6.7 million for fiscal 1994, down 13% from 
the previous year's revenues of $7.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company has been in turmoil since Lee Mannheimer, the firm's longtime 
chief executive officer, resigned in the fall amid an investigation into his 
possible role in an alleged murder-for-hire plot against his estranged wife. 
Joseph Mazin, the company's controlling shareholder, took over as CEO in 
November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
