<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: MISSION PRODUCE TO MARKET IRVINE AVOCADOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mission Produce Inc., an Oxnard avocado distributor, has signed a $7-million 
contract to market avocados grown in Orange County by Newport Beach-based 
Irvine Co. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission, which represents more than 1,000 California growers, will market all 
4 million pounds of avocados produced by Irvine from now until the end of the 
year, according to Mission President Steve Barnard. 
</P>
<P>
 "Irvine is the biggest independent avocado grower in California," Barnard 
said. "We hope to have an ongoing relationship with them." 
</P>
<P>
 Mission will open an office in Orange County to service the new contract. The 
company's annual sales exceed $50 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
