<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: CALIFORNIA AMPLIFIER JOINS WIRELESS CABLE TV ALLIANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Camarillo-based California Amplifier Inc. is one of six firms that have formed 
an alliance to develop digital technology for the wireless cable television 
industry. The group is headed by Zenith Electronics Corp. and American 
Telecasting Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 California Amplifier hopes to gain a stake in wireless systems that could 
someday compete with cable by offering viewers hundreds of TV channels. 
</P>
<P>
 The alliance will also investigate offering pay-per-view movies, wireless 
telephone service, interactive games and home shopping, reports Ira (Ike) 
Coron, California Amplifier's newly named chairman and chief executive. 
</P>
<P>
 "It won't affect our sales or earnings for some time, but we hope it will 
bring the possibilities for wireless into perspective," Coron said. 
</P>
<P>
 California Amplifier produces components used in distributing TV signals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
